In the following part of the Gear VR Quick Start, we will go over how to launch your UE4 project so that it can be viewed with the Gear VR HMD.

## Steps

1. First, make sure that your Samsung Galaxy Smartphone is connected to your development PC via a USB cable and that your PC can see the device using the **ADB** command **ADB Devices**.

1. From the Main Toolbar, click on the small white triangle next to the **Launch** icon, to open the **Options for Launching on a Device**.

    [REGION:lightbox]
    [![](GVR_Deploy_To_Android.png)(w:550)](GVR_Deploy_To_Android.png)
    [/REGION]

    [REGION:caption]
    Click for full image.
    [/REGION]

1. From the Main Toolbar, click on the small white triangle next to the **Launch** icon, to open the **Options for Launching on a Device**.

    [REGION:lightbox]
    [![](GVR_Deployed_Files.png)(w:550)](GVR_Deployed_Files.png)
    [/REGION]

    [REGION:caption]
    Click for full image.
    [/REGION]

    [region:note]
    If prompted to save, make sure that you do even if you just saved before to ensure that the latest content makes it onto your device.
    [/region]

1. Check in the lower corner of the UE4 Editor; a progress window will be displayed that will tell you what stage the packaging is currently on. If this is the first time you are packing your project, this could take a few minutes depending on the size of your project. 

    [REGION:lightbox]
    [![](GVR_Deployment_Window.png)(w:550)](GVR_Deployment_Window.png)
    [/REGION]

    [REGION:caption]
    Click for full image.
    [/REGION]

    [region:note]
    To see detailed information about what is currently happing during the packing process, click on the **Show Output Log** link in the progress window.
    [/region]

1. When the packing and installing process has completed, a notification will be displayed, and a sound will be played. You can then put your device in your Gear VR HMD and when you put it on you should something similar to the following video.

